        "## 16. Equations of planes in space"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "SsPDstgSOnqx"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "1. The plane passes through points $A(1, 2, 3)$, $B(3, 4, 5)$, and $C(2, 1, 4)$. Find the equation of the plane.\n",
        "\n",
        "The equation of the plane can be written as:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "ax + by + cz = d\n",
        "$$\n",
        "First, find the vectors $\\overrightarrow{AB}$ and $\\overrightarrow{AC}$:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\overrightarrow{AB} = B - A = (3 - 1, 4 - 2, 5 - 3) = (2, 2, 2)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\overrightarrow{AC} = C - A = (2 - 1, 1 - 2, 4 - 3) = (1, -1, 1)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "Now, compute the cross product $\\overrightarrow{AB} \\times \\overrightarrow{AC}$ to find the normal vector of the plane:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\overrightarrow{AB} \\times \\overrightarrow{AC} = \\begin{vmatrix} \\mathbf{i} & \\mathbf{j} & \\mathbf{k} \\\\ 2 & 2 & 2 \\\\ 1 & -1 & 1 \\end{vmatrix}\n",
        "= \\mathbf{i}(2 \\cdot 1 - 2 \\cdot 1) - \\mathbf{j}(2 \\cdot 1 - 2 \\cdot 1) + \\mathbf{k}(2 \\cdot (-1) - 2 \\cdot 1)\n",
        "= \\mathbf{i}(0) - \\mathbf{j}(0) + \\mathbf{k}(-4)\n",
        "= (0, 0, -4)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "So the normal vector is $(0, 0, -4)$, and the equation of the plane is:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "0(x - 1) + 0(y - 2) - 4(z - 3) = 0\n",
        "$$\n",
        "which simplifies to:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "z = 3\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "2. The plane passes through point $A(1, 2, 3)$ and is parallel to the plane $2x + 3y + 4z = 5$. Find the equation of the plane.\n",
        "\n",
        "The normal vector of the given plane is $(2, 3, 4)$. Since the new plane is parallel to this, it has the same normal vector. The equation of the plane is:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "2(x - 1) + 3(y - 2) + 4(z - 3) = 0\n",
        "$$\n",
        "Expanding:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "2x - 2 + 3y - 6 + 4z - 12 = 0\n",
        "$$\n",
        "which simplifies to:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "2x + 3y + 4z = 20\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "3. The plane passes through point $A(1, 2, 3)$ and is perpendicular to the normal vector $\\mathbf{n} = [2, 3, 4]$. Find the equation of the plane.\n",
        "\n",
        "Since the plane is perpendicular to the normal vector $\\mathbf{n} = (2, 3, 4)$, the equation of the plane is:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "2(x - 1) + 3(y - 2) + 4(z - 3) = 0\n",
        "$$\n",
        "Expanding:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "2x - 2 + 3y - 6 + 4z - 12 = 0\n",
        "$$\n",
        "which simplifies to:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "2x + 3y + 4z = 20\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "4. We have two planes $2x + 3y + 4z = 5$ and $3x + 4y + 2z = 6$. Find the line of intersection of these planes.\n",
        "\n",
        "The line of intersection of two planes is given by the cross product of their normal vectors. The normal vectors are:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\mathbf{n_1} = (2, 3, 4), \\quad \\mathbf{n_2} = (3, 4, 2)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "Find the cross product:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\mathbf{n_1} \\times \\mathbf{n_2} = \\begin{vmatrix} \\mathbf{i} & \\mathbf{j} & \\mathbf{k} \\\\ 2 & 3 & 4 \\\\ 3 & 4 & 2 \\end{vmatrix}\n",
        "= \\mathbf{i}(3 \\cdot 2 - 4 \\cdot 4) - \\mathbf{j}(2 \\cdot 2 - 4 \\cdot 3) + \\mathbf{k}(2 \\cdot 4 - 3 \\cdot 3)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "$$\n",
        "= \\mathbf{i}(6 - 16) - \\mathbf{j}(4 - 12) + \\mathbf{k}(8 - 9)\n",
        "= \\mathbf{i}(-10) - \\mathbf{j}(-8) + \\mathbf{k}(-1)\n",
        "= (-10, 8, -1)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "Thus, the direction vector of the line of intersection is $(-10, 8, -1)$. To find a point on the line, solve the system of equations:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "2x + 3y + 4z = 5, \\quad 3x + 4y + 2z = 6\n",
        "$$\n",
        "You can solve this system by substitution or elimination.\n",
        "\n",
        "5. Write the equation of the plane passing through point $A(1, 2, 3)$ and parallel to vectors $\\vec{v_1} = [1, 0, 1]$ and $\\vec{v_2} = [0, 1, -1]$.\n",
        "\n",
        "The normal vector to the plane is the cross product of the two given vectors:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\vec{v_1} \\times \\vec{v_2} = \\begin{vmatrix} \\mathbf{i} & \\mathbf{j} & \\mathbf{k} \\\\ 1 & 0 & 1 \\\\ 0 & 1 & -1 \\end{vmatrix}\n",
        "= \\mathbf{i}(0 \\cdot (-1) - 1 \\cdot 1) - \\mathbf{j}(1 \\cdot (-1) - 1 \\cdot 0) + \\mathbf{k}(1 \\cdot 1 - 0 \\cdot 0)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "$$\n",
        "= \\mathbf{i}(-1) - \\mathbf{j}(-1) + \\mathbf{k}(1)\n",
        "= (-1, 1, 1)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "So the normal vector is $(-1, 1, 1)$. The equation of the plane is:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "-1(x - 1) + 1(y - 2) + 1(z - 3) = 0\n",
        "$$\n",
        "Expanding:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "-x + 1 + y - 2 + z - 3 = 0\n",
        "$$\n",
        "which simplifies to:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "-x + y + z = 4\n",
        "$$\n",
        "or\n",
        "$$\n",
        "x - y - z = -4\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "6. We have the plane $2x + 3y + 4z = 5$. Find an example of a plane parallel and perpendicular to it.\n",
        "\n",
        "- Parallel plane: Any plane parallel to $2x + 3y + 4z = 5$ will have the same normal vector $(2, 3, 4)$. For example, the plane:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "2x + 3y + 4z = 10\n",
        "$$\n",
        "is parallel to the given plane.\n",
        "\n",
        "- Perpendicular plane: A plane perpendicular to $2x + 3y + 4z = 5$ will have a normal vector that is perpendicular to $(2, 3, 4)$. For example, the plane:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "x + y + z = 0\n",
        "$$\n",
        "is perpendicular to the given plane because the dot product of the normal vectors $(2, 3, 4)$ and $(1, 1, 1)$ is 0.\n",
        "\n",
        "7. We have the plane $2x + 3y + 4z = 5$ and point $A(1, 2, 3)$. Find the distance from point $A$ to this plane.\n",
        "\n",
        "The distance from a point $(x_1, y_1, z_1)$ to the plane $ax + by + cz + d = 0$ is given by the formula:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\text{Distance} = \\frac{|ax_1 + by_1 + cz_1 + d|}{\\sqrt{a^2 + b^2 + c^2}}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "For the plane $2x + 3y + 4z - 5 = 0$ and point $A(1, 2, 3)$:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\text{Distance} = \\frac{|2(1) + 3(2) + 4(3) - 5|}{\\sqrt{2^2 + 3^2 + 4^2}}\n",
        "= \\frac{|2 + 6 + 12 - 5|}{\\sqrt{4 + 9 + 16}}\n",
        "= \\frac{|15|}{\\sqrt{29}} = \\frac{15}{\\sqrt{29}}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "8. The plane intersects the coordinate axes at points $A(2, 0, 0)$, $B(0, 3, 0)$, and $C(0, 0, 4)$. Find the equation of the plane.\n",
        "\n",
        "The intercept form of the equation of a plane is:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{x}{a} + \\frac{y}{b} + \\frac{z}{c} = 1\n",
        "$$\n",
        "where $a$, $b$, and $c$ are the intercepts with the $x$, $y$, and $z$ axes, respectively. The intercepts are given by the points:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "a = 2, \\quad b = 3, \\quad c = 4\n",
        "$$\n",
        "Thus, the equation of the plane is:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{x}{2} + \\frac{y}{3} + \\frac{z}{4} = 1\n",
        "$$\n",
        "or equivalently:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "6x + 4y + 3z = 24\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "9. Calculate the angle between the plane $x + y + z = 1$ and the plane $x = 0$ (i.e., the $yz$ plane).\n",
        "\n",
        "The normal vector to the plane $x + y + z = 1$ is $(1, 1, 1)$, and the normal vector to the plane $x = 0$ is $(1, 0, 0)$. The angle between two planes is given by the angle between their normal vectors. Using the formula:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\cos \\theta = \\frac{\\mathbf{n_1} \\cdot \\mathbf{n_2}}{|\\mathbf{n_1}| |\\mathbf{n_2}|}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "where $\\mathbf{n_1} = (1, 1, 1)$ and $\\mathbf{n_2} = (1, 0, 0)$:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\mathbf{n_1} \\cdot \\mathbf{n_2} = 1 \\cdot 1 + 1 \\cdot 0 + 1 \\cdot 0 = 1\n",
        "$$\n",
        "$$\n",
        "|\\mathbf{n_1}| = \\sqrt{1^2 + 1^2 + 1^2} = \\sqrt{3}, \\quad |\\mathbf{n_2}| = \\sqrt{1^2} = 1\n",
        "$$\n",
        "Thus:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\cos \\theta = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}} \\quad \\Rightarrow \\quad \\theta = \\cos^{-1}\\left(\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}\\right)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "10. Find the vector perpendicular to the plane $x + y + z = 1$.\n",
        "\n",
        "The normal vector to the plane $x + y + z = 1$ is the vector of coefficients of $x$, $y$, and $z$, which is:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "(1, 1, 1)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "Thus, the vector perpendicular to the plane is $(1, 1, 1)$.\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
